Subject: Re: [T2] Swapped alternator, lost parts

On Aug 18, 2005, at 7:14 PM, Mark Dominesey wrote:

> In my 74 w/ 2L, I finally swapped my alternator that had an internal
> short.  In the process of doing that, I lost the little plug thing  
> that
> covers the alternator tightening bolt,

021-119-295 is what you want. BD used to have them but their part  
number seems corrupted. Call.

http://busdepot.com/details.jsp?partnumber=02111929501C

> I lost the fancy alternator
> tightening nut,

The t-slot nut is 021-903-243A

http://busdepot.com/details.jsp?partnumber=021903243A

> and I lost the grommet that seals the dipstick through the
> tin.  I also lost several engine tin Bolts.

That grommet is NLA. Just seal it up with silicone.

